Definition.WordDefinition: tchotchke \tchotch"ke\ n. 1. [Yiddish tshatshke, trinket, from Pol. czaczko. --MW10.] a knickknack or trinket; a decorative item or souvenir of little value. [Also spelled {chotchke}.] [PJC]
tchotchke n 1: (Yiddish) a mistress [syn: {chachka}] 2: (Yiddish) an inexpensive showy trinket [syn: {chachka}]
